spirit:addressBlock.spirit:name: some_register_map
spirit:addressBlock.spirit:description: This address map contains some example registers to show how RDL can be utilized in various situations.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CLKEN_BK0
spirit:field.spirit:description: clock enable bk 0, doesn't used in cp920

spirit:field.spirit:name: CAMOVE
spirit:field.spirit:description: bk0 enable come from sw_camenable when it set, else come from fuse.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ROM_WAIT_CYCLE
spirit:field.spirit:description: rom wait cycle 0x0 = 3 wait cycles 0x1 = 2 wait cycles 0x2 = 1 wait cycle 0x3 = no wait cycle

spirit:field.spirit:name: CLKEN_BK2
spirit:field.spirit:description: clock enable bk 2, doesn't used in 920

spirit:field.spirit:name: CLKEN_BK1
spirit:field.spirit:description: clock enable bk 1, doesn't used in 920

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQU_FMBIST_SW_CAM_ACC_EN
spirit:field.spirit:description: squ fmbist software cam access enable

spirit:field.spirit:name: OTP_SQU_MUX_SEL
spirit:field.spirit:description: otp_squ_mux_sel this field selects which fuse block to read.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CLKEN_BK4
spirit:field.spirit:description: clock enable bk 4, doesn't used in cp920

spirit:field.spirit:name: CLKEN_BK3
spirit:field.spirit:description: clock enable bk 3, doesn't used in cp920

spirit:field.spirit:name: PWRDONE
spirit:field.spirit:description: power down for bank4-bank0, corresponding bits are 28-24

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_AUTORESP_TYPE230
spirit:field.spirit:description: timeout auto response type 0 = auto response type is slverr 1 = auto response type is okay

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_AUTORESP_EN231
spirit:field.spirit:description: timeout auto response enable 0 = disable auto response when fabric timeout happens 1 = enable auto response when fabric timeout happens

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_TIMEOUT_INT_MSK233
spirit:field.spirit:description: timeout interrupt mask 0 = interrupt is not masked 1 = interrupt is masked

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_FAB_MON_RST236
spirit:field.spirit:description: fabric monitor reset 0 = reset fabric monitor 1 = release fabric monitor

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_FAB_MON_CLR237
spirit:field.spirit:description: clear the information saved when last time timeout occurs 0 = the relevant registers are kept 1 = the relevant registers are cleared

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_TIMEOUT_VAL239
spirit:field.spirit:description: axi fabric timeout value this field indicates the timeout value for axi fabric. the unit of measure is one axi clock cycle.

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_STATE_HOLD_CTRL249
spirit:field.spirit:description: controlling bit of holding the registers' contents after functional reset. 0 = the registers will not update the status in real time and the values in the registers are not valid. 1 = the registers will be updated to the read state in time. once reset is asserted, the state_hold_ctrl[0] will be cleared and the registers will hold the values just before reset.

spirit:register.spirit:description: Real Time AXI Fabric Timeout Transaction ID Register

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_WR_TIMEOUT_IND257
spirit:field.spirit:description: write timeout indicator 0 = no write request timeout 1 = write request timeout happens

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_TIMEOUT_TX_WID259
spirit:field.spirit:description: the wid of write transaction which causes first timeout event. it is only valid when bit[31], wr_timeout_ind is asserted

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_RD_TIMEOUT_IND260
spirit:field.spirit:description: read timeout indicator 0 = no read request timeout 1 = read request timeout happens

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_TIMEOUT_TX_RID262

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_WR_TIMEOUT_IND272

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_CAUSE291
spirit:field.spirit:description: dvc cause this field is the cause of the current ongoing dvc. it is only valid when the <voltage change status> field is 1. 0x1 = <var processor: application mp> software-triggered dvc 0x2 = <var processor: comm> software- triggered dvc 0x4 = <var processor: msa> software- triggered dvc 0x8 = hw-dfc triggered dvc others = lpm entry/exit trigger dvc

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_DVC_STATUS297
spirit:field.spirit:description: voltage change status the voltage change may be triggered in active state or entering low power mode. 0 = there is no voltage change or a voltage change has finished 1 = voltage change is in progress

spirit:field.spirit:description: dclk dfc cause this field is the cause of the current ongoing dfc. it is only valid when the <dclk_dfc_status> field is 1. 0x1 = <var processor: application mp> triggered dfc 0x2 = <var processor: comm> triggered dfc in active mode 0x4 = msa trigged dfc in active mode 0x8 = gnss triggered dfc in active mode others = low power mode entry/exit triggered dfc

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_DFC_STATUS309
spirit:field.spirit:description: dclk dfc status the dclk dfc may be triggered in active state or <var processor: seagull/msa> entering low power mode. 0 = there is no dfc or dfc has finished 1 = dfc is in progress

spirit:field.spirit:name: BYTECNT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 0 byte count number of bytes of data that this dma channel must transfer.

spirit:field.spirit:name: BYTECNT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 1 byte count number of bytes of data that this dma channel must transfer.

spirit:field.spirit:name: NDPTR0
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 0 next descriptor pointer address this must be 16 byte aligned.

spirit:field.spirit:name: NDPTR1
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 1 next descriptor pointer address this must be 16 byte aligned.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ABR819
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel abort when software sets this bit to 1, the dma aborts in the middle. this field is cleared by the dma hardware.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CDE821
spirit:field.spirit:description: close descriptor enable if enabled, the dma writes the remainder byte count into bits[31:16] of the byte count field. 0 = disable 1 = enable

spirit:field.spirit:name: SQ_SDA823
spirit:field.spirit:description: source/destination address alignment 0 = alignment is towards the source. after the dma's first read, all reads will be to 32-bit word aligned address. 1 = alignment is towards the destination. after the first write, the following writes will be with all byte enables asserted.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CHANACT824
spirit:field.spirit:description: dma channel active 0 = channel is not active 1 = channel is active

spirit:field.spirit:name: FETCHND825
spirit:field.spirit:description: fetch next descriptor 1 = forces a fetch of the next descriptor this field is automatically cleared after the fetch completes.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CHANEN826
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel enable when software sets this field to 1, it activates the channel.and this bit will automatically cleared after the dma transfer is done setting it to 0 causes the channel to suspend. re-setting this field to 1 allows the channel to continue dma transfer.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INTMODE829
spirit:field.spirit:description: interrupt mode 0 = interrupt asserted every time the dma byte count reaches 0 1 = interrupt asserted when the next descriptor pointer value is null and the dma byte count reaches 0

spirit:field.spirit:name: CHAINMOD830
spirit:field.spirit:description: chain mode 0 = chain mode 1 = non-chain mode

spirit:field.spirit:name: BURSTLIMIT831
spirit:field.spirit:description: burst limit in each dma access 0x5 = 1 byte 0x6 = 2 bytes 0x0 = 4 bytes 0x1 = 8 bytes 0x3 = 16 bytes 0x7 = 32 bytes

spirit:field.spirit:name: DESTDIR832
spirit:field.spirit:description: destination direction 0x0 = increment destination address 0x1 = decrement destination address 0x2 = hold in the same value 0x3 = reserved

spirit:field.spirit:name: SRCDIR833
spirit:field.spirit:description: source direction 0x0 = increment source address 0x1 = decrement source address 0x2 = hold in the same value 0x3 = reserved

spirit:field.spirit:name: ABR843
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel abort when software sets this bit to 1, the dma aborts in the middle. this field is cleared by the dma hardware.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CDE845
spirit:field.spirit:description: close descriptor enable if enabled, the dma writes the remainder byte count into bits[31:16] of the byte count field. 0 = disable 1 = enable

spirit:field.spirit:name: CHANACT847
spirit:field.spirit:description: dma channel active 0 = channel is not active 1 = channel is active

spirit:field.spirit:name: FETCHND848
spirit:field.spirit:description: fetch next descriptor 1 = forces a fetch of the next descriptor this field is automatically cleared after the fetch completes.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CHANEN849
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel enable when software sets this field to 1, it activates the channel.and this bit will automatically cleared after the dma transfer is done setting it to 0 causes the channel to suspend. re-setting this field to 1 allows the channel to continue dma transfer.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INTMODE852
spirit:field.spirit:description: interrupt mode 0 = interrupt asserted every time the dma byte count reaches 0 1 = interrupt asserted when the next descriptor pointer value is null and the dma byte count reaches 0

spirit:field.spirit:name: CHAINMOD853
spirit:field.spirit:description: chain mode 0 = chain mode 1 = non-chain mode

spirit:field.spirit:name: BURSTLIMIT854
spirit:field.spirit:description: burst limit in each dma access 0x5 = 1 byte 0x6 = 2 bytes 0x0 = 4 bytes 0x1 = 8 bytes 0x3 = 16 bytes 0x7 = 32 bytes

spirit:field.spirit:name: DESTDIR855
spirit:field.spirit:description: destination direction 0x0 = increment destination address 0x1 = decrement destination address 0x2 = hold in the same value 0x3 = reserved

spirit:field.spirit:name: SRCDIR856
spirit:field.spirit:description: source direction 0x0 = increment source address 0x1 = decrement source address 0x2 = hold in the same value 0x3 = reserved

spirit:field.spirit:name: REVERSE_MEMORY_COPY
spirit:field.spirit:description: reverse memory copy 0x1= when <srcdir>/<destdir> is 2'b01 and the current size left in channel is equal to or less than burst limit in each dma access, the current dma source/destination address = (channel source/destination addr - current left size) 0x0= current dma source/destination address use normal source/destination address

spirit:field.spirit:name: PRIOCHAN10
spirit:field.spirit:description: channels 0 and 1 priority 0x0 = round robin 0x1 = priority to channel 1 over channel 0 0x2 = priority to channel 0 over channel 1 0x3 = reserved

spirit:field.spirit:name: RSR0
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 0 reset select address the bits in this register correspond to the bits in the chan_0_int_status register. setting a bit to 1 will enable its corresponding chan_0_int_status bit read clear function.

spirit:field.spirit:name: RSR1
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 1 reset select address the bits in this register correspond to the bits in the chan_1_int_status register. setting a bit to 1 enables its corresponding chan_1_int_status bit read clear function.

spirit:field.spirit:name: DMA_ABORT_INT927
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 0 dma aborted interrupt mask 1 = channel 0 dma aborted interrupt is enabled

spirit:field.spirit:name: COMP928
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 0 interrupt mask 1 = channel 0 comp interrupt is enabled

spirit:field.spirit:name: DMA_ABORT_INT936
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 1 dma aborted interrupt mask 1 = channel 1 dma aborted interrupt is enabled

spirit:field.spirit:name: COMP937
spirit:field.spirit:description: channel 1 interrupt mask 1 = channel 1 comp interrupt is enabled

spirit:field.spirit:name: DMA_ABORT945
spirit:field.spirit:description: dma abort interrupt status and clear channel 0 read clear in this field is enabled through the corresponding rsr bit setting in the chan_0_rsr register.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT_DONE946
spirit:field.spirit:description: interrupt done channel 0 read clear in this field is enabled through the corresponding rsr bit setting in the chan_0_rsr register.

spirit:field.spirit:name: DMA_ABORT954
spirit:field.spirit:description: dma abort interrupt status and clear channel 0 read clear in this field is enabled through the corresponding rsr bit setting in the chan_1_rsr register.

spirit:field.spirit:name: INT_DONE955
spirit:field.spirit:description: interrupt done channel 0 read clear in this field is enabled through the corresponding rsr bit setting in the chan_1_rsr register.
